      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The tech industry argues that heavy regulation stifles innovation by imposing burdensome compliance costs and slowing down the pace of research. They contend that overly prescriptive rules risk locking in current technologies, preventing the development of potentially revolutionary, future AI capabilities. Furthermore, they suggest that self-governance and industry-led best practices are more agile and effective at managing risks than slow, bureaucratic government mandates.",
